reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 3+ years and holding strong!!
reviews.reviewText: We bought this when we moved into our new house in September 2019, I’m writing this review in December 2022. So a full 3+ years later, and it still works great and has always looked fantastic! Not to mention it’s super simple to use. Absolutely recommend for anyone looking for a microwave that is also a conversation piece.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Looking Microwave
reviews.reviewText: We are really enjoying this microwave. Our over stove built in failed on New Year’s Eve. I ordered this red countertop microwave to hold us over until I could have a new one installed. I figured if it wasn’t going to take up counter space, it ought to enhance the look of the kitchen. The family loves it and wants a red over stove microwave now. It is less noisy than our other microwave so I’m not sure what the other reviewers consider too noisy or loud. My main issue is that is has a lower wattage than we are accustomed to so it takes longer to heat up our food. Also, it scratches easily so be gentle with it. So far so good as we have had it a month and it gets used several times a day by our large household.Edited to add: It’s been a year, and we are still happy with our purchase. The microwave is being used several times a day and is still going strong.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great and love the design!
reviews.reviewText: I LOVE LOVE LOVE my little red retro microwave. It perfectly compliments my matching nostalgia red toaster and my red mini keurig brewer. Ive been without a microwave for several years and truthfully have not missed it. I just started a meal plan though to get myself back together after working nightshift in covid icu feb-august. Since ill have some pre made meals, this makes it easier. I love the look, it heats evenly and quickly, not too loud, easy controls. Did i mention I LOVE the look?? 👍

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 1, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Noisy but super cute... til it DIES
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Adorable microwave, looks exactly as shown and is supper simple to use! Basic controls which we love. The biggest issue is the noise, it operates loud as you can hear in our video.UPDATE: 13 months later and it is DEAD... was microwaving eggs and smelled something strange, when I opened the microwave the seal was melted/burned.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I love it and it looks so great in my kitchen!! The only thing is it's a pull open model instead of pushing a button to open. So because if the weight distribution, when I would pull it open when it was on the shelf I had my previous microwave on, it kept pulling it partially off the shelf. I moved it to the counter and it would still move everytime I opened it. So I ended up putting some cushioning under it from the packaging and that stopped most of the moving forward. It's powerful. The last microwave I had was 200 watts stringer than this one, but this one cooks better, quicker, and more evenly. Did I mention how good it looks??! Totally worth the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute as a button
reviews.reviewText: I love everything about it, the ease of use, the way it looks, the compact design----HOWEVER, if cooking things super fast is really important to you, this isn't the microwave for you. I don't mind. In fact, it seems to cook things better as in, you don't get that "cold in the middle/piping hot on the outside" syndrome. But let's say you had a frozen dinner. My last microwave almost overcooked it in 4 mins. This one takes 5-6 mins. That's fine with me but if you are impatient, you'd be better off with a 1200 watt.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great retro look, good microwave with nice quick program dial... no mute feature.
reviews.reviewText: The appearance and design aesthetics are great for a retro theme and/or specific color coordination. We purchased this for our in-home office kitchen, along with the matching toaster. The metallic color is rich and vibrant but tactful. The quick program dial is useful and I personally like the circular clock display (I wish it had military 24 hour time as an option, but it does not). The only lacking quality is the ability to turn the sound off, which is quite a common feature now for microwaves at all price levels. It should be standard on a product at this price point and I was close to dropping a star based on that. However, we are so delighted with the overall product we applied 5 stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very cool-looking and sturdy microwave oven!
reviews.reviewText: With plenty of useful dials and buttons, this cool, 50s-style retro microwave oven serves its purpose and looks great in my kitchen. Seems to be pretty sturdy as well. My only complaint is that the three beeps that tell you something is cooked are extremely loud! Otherwise, a nice kitchen tool.
